<http://www.GideonOnline.com>

Background information on typhoid and paratyphoid in Tajikistan
-----------------------------------------------------
1865 cases were reported in 1996;
an estimated 24 000 during 1996 to 1999;
7335 in 1999;
4415 in 2000.
(Rates per 100 000:
118.3 in 1999;
70.7 in 2000)
An epidemic (most in Kulyab; 34 percent below age 14) was reported
during May-Jun 1996. This and subsequent outbreaks numbered almost
4000 cases and were ascribed to a breakdown in drinking water supply
following dissolution of the USSR.
During 1997, an outbreak of multidrug-resistant typhoid fever spread
from Dushanbe (8 901 cases, 95 fatal) to Kulyab and Tursunzade;
municipal water was identified as the source.
An outbreak of over 500 cases (3 fatal) was reported in Dushanbe in 2003.
52 typhoid fatalities were reported in 1981;
46 in 1982;
32 in 1985;
44 in 1986;
36 in 1987;
22 in 1988;
19 in 1989;
15 in 1990;
10 in 1992.
89 cases of paratyphoid were reported in 1999; 60 in 2000.
(Rates per 100 000: 1.4 in 1999; 0.9 in 2000)
--
Steve Berger
Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
